<br>
Next to Cheapest - Because of the high resale value and the low failure rate on the combines if sticking to things that are barely trivial and the resale of some items to players this one is cheaper to get to 250 then any other trade skill (don't beleive me look what some things cost for a simple combine to get smithing or pottery or tailoring or baking to even move an inch past 200).<br>
<br>
Easiest - Jewel craft is easiest because all you have to do is give your character a few thousand plat and sit in one spot sece you can buy everything you need from any jewelcraft merchants wich normaly are right next to eachuther.  Also easiest because every single combine only takes a bar of metal and a gem.  No combining 50 things for one skill up.<br>
<br>
Fastest - Out of all the skills I worked on to get high enuff t complete the 8th coldain shawl this one had the most skill ups per combine even past the 150- 160 point were many skills started taking 40-50 combines for one skill up (Cough, fletching).<br>
<br>
Brewing is the cheapest sence you can get it to 250 making mino hero brew (unless the trivial got changed on it) which requires cheap items from merchants, but isn't easier then jewelcraft or faster because it takes like 7-8 items for one combine and skill ups arn't as fast.<br>
<br>
(Note) - I don't count fishing as a trade skill even though it might fall in the catagory of trade skills.  I see fishing more as a secondary skill like swimming. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gyarus>Gyarus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/26/03 12:46:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26254.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Re: re:Tradeskills &amp; stat</span><hr size=1> Personally I took smithing to 250.<br>
<br>
Now why would a human wizard do that?  Simply put I love tradeskills.  You can only kite so many mobs before it is boring.  Tradskills are a nice break.  I've done the shawl quests, yes the item is great.<br>
<br>
With smithing I've made hundreds of thousands of plat.  Have a level 30 bard in a full suit of fierce heraldic armor, etc.  But this came at a price.  Some skills, bakeing and brewing for example, are fast and cheap.  Others start easy and get hard at 180 or so (JC, Pottery).  Then there is tailoring and smithing.  Never will any skill force you to kill more green mobs or want to pull your hair out.  They skill up slow, require tons of farming and/or tons of plat.<br>
<br>
My advice is do tradskills only if you enjoy them, or semi do them for the shawl.  They can be tedious and time consuming.  You'll lose lots of xp time GMing some of them.  The reason so many PoP tradeskill items are nice are because even at max skill sucess rates are low.  Never think there is one tradeskill you &quot;have&quot; to do.  Pick one and try it, if you do not like the time you are spending with it, then stop.  A tradeskiller is just another type of player.  Some people prefer to spend time collecting AA's, some prefer killing uber_mob_01, some like tradeskills, some like..... Find what you like and do that.  And as always www.eqtraders.com is the best site for tradeskills, period.<br>
<br>
Gyarus Glowinghand<br>
